http://dbpedia.org/resource/Natalie_Coughlin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Natalie Coughlin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Natalie_Coughlin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Natalie_Coughlin\"}, {\"begin\": 867, \"end\": 881, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Thompson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jenny Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Thompson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 27-year-old now has eight golds, four silvers and one bronze over four Olympics, with every intention of swimming on to Los Angeles in 2028.\", \"from\": 883, \"to\": 1027, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1007, \"end\": 1018, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999991568664798, \"rank\": 8.430634988892674e-07, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McIntosh cruised to victory in the 200 butterfly, dealing American Regan Smith a familiar silver-medal finish.\", \"from\": 1029, \"to\": 1139, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1029, \"end\": 1037, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 0.9999999999859028, \"rank\": 1.417481356132408e-11, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}, {\"begin\": 1087, \"end\": 1095, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9954358602038409, \"rank\": 0.003600036301005804, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", 